subaward_description:
IN SUPPORT OF THE LCMS ASSESSMENT, SUBCONTRACTOR SHALL:
 
 WORK WITH THE DIGITAL TEAM AND STAKEHOLDERS TO DEFINE THE OBJECTIVES FOR THE LMCS APPLICATION HOSTING ENVIRONMENT ASSESSMENT.
 DEVELOP REQUIREMENTS BACKLOG (2-004) IDENTIFYING ALL MIGRATION REQUIREMENTS WITHIN AN FFB DEDICATED JIRA REPOSITORY (TO ALSO BE APPLIED FOR PRODUCTION MIGRATION PROJECT) AS WELL AS APPLICATION LIFECYCLE MANAGEMENT (ALM) REQUIREMENTS FOR ATLASSIAN SUITE DETERMINED FOR SETUP DURING THE ASSESSMENT PROJECT.
 DEVELOP AN INVENTORY (2-005) OF TECHNOLOGY AND DATA ASSETS IN ORDER TO ACCOUNT FOR ALL ASPECTS OF FFB HOSTING WITHIN WC2-H.
 PERFORM GAPS ANALYSIS BETWEEN THE FFB REQUIREMENTS AND NOTIONAL ARCHITECTURE AND THE ANTICIPATED WC2-H ENVIRONMENT AND DOCUMENT IN GAP ANALYSIS REPORT (2-006).
 USE THE DISCOVERED OBJECTIVES, UNDERSTANDINGS, INPUTS AND ASSUMPTIONS, COUPLED WITH THE PRELIMINARY AGREED UPON SET OF TOOLS AND TECHNOLOGIES, TO DEVELOP A LIST OF FEATURES (FROM A TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION PERSPECTIVE), A TARGET STATE ARCHITECTURAL DIAGRAM THAT DEFINES THE PROPOSED TECHNOLOGY STACK IN A COMPLETED VISUAL FORM, AND THE OVERALL WRITTEN APPROACH TO IMPLEMENTATION OF THE LMCS (2-008).
 THE SCOPE OF THE DATALAKE PROJECT INCLUDES THE PLANNING, IMPLEMENTATION, TESTING, AND DEPLOYMENT OF THE DATALAKE INTO THE WC2-H ENVIRONMENT, AS OUTLINED IN THE  FS DATALAKE ASSESSMENT AND ROADMAP. 
 ASSESSMENT, MIGRATION, SA&A SUPPORT AND ONGOING OPERATIONS AND MAINTENANCE SUPPORT FOR THE DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY APPLICATION IN THE WORKPLACE.GOV COMMUNITY CLOUD (WC2).
 THIS EFFORT IS FOR THE DEVELOPMENT & IMPLEMENTATION OF DERIVED PIV CAPABILITY IN WC2 HIGH CLOUD ENVIRONMENT. EBS HAS IDENTIFIED A NEED FOR PROFESSIONAL SERVICES TO HELP IMPLEMENT THE FEDRAMP HIGH SOLUTION DERIVED PIV (ENTRUST IDENTITY GUARD SOLUTION) CAPABILITY.
 
 SUBCONTRACTOR SHALL USE THE FINAL FEDRAMP HIGH IMPLEMENTATION BLUEPRINT AND FINAL FEDRAMP HIGH CSP CONCEPTUAL ARCHITECTURE AS REFERENCE DOCUMENTS FOR THIS PROJECT.

SUBCONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE PROFESSIONAL CONSULTANTS TO JOIN IEP PORTAL.  THROUGHOUT THE COURSE OF THE CONTRACT, THE SUBCONTRACTOR PROFESSIONAL CONSULTANTS SHALL PARTICIPATE IN TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE WORK SESSIONS FOR THE EXISTING AND FUTURE PORTAL DESIGN.  THE SUBCONTRACTOR PROFESSIONALS WILL ASSIST WITH DETAILED DESIGN CREATION AND BUILD-OUT OF THE TRANSACTIONAL PORTAL ENVIRONMENT. THE SUBCONTRACTOR PROFESSIONAL CONSULTANTS SHALL REVIEW, MENTOR, AND PROVIDE TECHNICAL GUIDANCE TO OTHER PROJECT TEAM MEMBERS AS APPROPRIATE.  
 
 RESOURCES:  JEANNE TIAN 
 
 REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS/RESPONSIBILITIES:
   DEEP KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE OF API GATEWAY ARCHITECTURE 
   RESPONSIBLE FOR THE INSTALLATION, MAINTENANCE AND TROUBLESHOOTING OF VIRTUAL AND HARDWARE FORUM SENTRY API GATEWAYS
   DESIGN AND VALIDATE FORUM SENTRY POLICIES THAT INCLUDE THREAT MITIGATION, TRANSACTION PRIVACY AND TRANSACTION INTEGRITY 
   KNOWLEDGE OF SITEMINDER AUTHENTICATION, SOAP/REST WEB SERVICES, INTEGRATION MESSAGING PATTERNS AND MUTUAL AUTHENTICATION (PKI)
   KNOWLEDGE OF IRS MEF APPLICATION ARCHITECTURE (FRONT-END AND BACKEND)
 
 
 RESOURCES:  JULIO HERNANDEZ 
 
 REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS/RESPONSIBILITIES:
   STRONG EXPERIENCE IN WAN/LAN INFRASTRUCTURE
   SOLID KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERIENCE IN NETWORK INTRUSION DETECTION SYSTEM (NIDS) PROTOCOLS
   STRONG NETWORK KNOWLEDGE/EXPERIENCE IN ROUTER CONFIGURATION AND ROUTING PROTOCOLS
   KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE IN SOFTWARE DEPLOYMENT, AND MONITORING
   KNOWLEDGE OF CISCO, F5, AND PALO ALTO NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE
   ABLE TO ACQUIRE AND IMPLEMENT NETWORK CONFIGURATION AND TROUBLESHOOTING SKILLS FOR SDDC.
 
 RESOURCES:  CHARLES FELIX
 
 REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS/RESPONSIBILITIES:
   STRONG EXPERIENCE IN LAN/WAN INFRASTRUCTURE
   STRONG F5, CISCO, AND FIREWALL EXPERIENCE
   STRONG NETWORK ROUTING/SWITCHING KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERIENCE
   STRONG NETWORK/TRAFFIC TROUBLESHOOTING AND PROBLEM SOLVING ISSUES
   ABLE TO ACQUIRE AND IMPLEMENT NETWORK CONFIGURATION AND TROUBLESHOOTING SKILLS FOR SDDC.
   EXPERIENCE PLANNING AND EXECUTING OPERATIONAL INFRASTRUCTURE UPGRADES
 
 RESOURCES:  VIDYA GUMPELLA 
 
 REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS/RESPONSIBILITIES:
   DEEP KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE OF API GATEWAY ARCHITECTURE 
   RESPONSIBLE FOR THE INSTALLATION, MAINTENANCE AND TROUBLESHOOTING OF VIRTUAL AND HARDWARE FORUM SENTRY API GATEWAYS

subaward_description:
PORTAL SERVICE AND PROGRAM INTEGRATION SERVICES TO OPERATE THE IRS ENVIRONMENT WITHIN SPECIFIED SCOPE, QUALITY,  TIME, AND COST OBJECTIVES.
 
 PORTAL SERVICE AND PROGRAM INTEGRATION SERVICES TO OPERATE THE IRS ENVIRONMENT WITHIN SPECIFIED SCOPE, QUALITY,  TIME, AND COST OBJECTIVES.
 
 BABU JAYARAMAN - THIS RESOURCE WILL BE PRIMARILY RESPONSIBLE TO PROVIDE OVERSIGHT AND EXPERTISE IN INSTALLING, SUPPORTING AND MAINTAINING JBOSS APPLICATION SERVERS. PROVIDE SUPPORT FOR VMWARE ENVIRONMENT BY CHANGING PERFORMANCE PARAMETERS WITH J2EE. DUTIES INCLUDE PROVIDING HANDS-ON ANALYSIS OF ISSUES, ISSUE REPORTING, AND INCIDENT MANAGEMENT. THIS RESOURCE WILL TRAIN OTHER OPERATORS ON SYSTEM PARAMETERS TO MEET NEEDS. PROVIDE INDEPTH INSIGHT INTO PERFORMANCE MANAGEMENT ISSUES, AND ASSIST WITH THE CORRECTION.
 
 THE RESOURCE WILL BE A SYSTEMS ARCHITECT IN SUPPORT OF THE IEP 1.5 PORTALS PROJECT & PRIME TASK ORDER 3 PROGRAM.
 
 REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS:
   DEEP KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE IN THE MANAGEMENT OF LARGE DISTRIBUTED SYSTEMS.
   KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE IN JBOSS CROSS-PLATFORM APPLICATION SERVER THAT UTILIZES J2EE TO SUPPORT A VMWARE (VIRTUAL) ENVIRONMENT.
   KNOWLEDGE OF APPLICATION SERVICES AND LOAD BALANCING TECHNIQUES.
 RESPONSIBILITIES:
   PROVIDE OVERSIGHT OF INSTALLATION AND MAINTENANCE THE JBOSS APPLICATION SERVER.
   ENSURE THE CORRECT IMPLEMENTATION OF APPLICATION AND SYSTEM UPDATES
   PROVIDE SYSTEM BASED KNOWLEDGE TO LEADERSHIP, PEERS, AND CLIENT REPRESENTATIVES.
 
 RAMON PAQUETTE   THE RESOURCE WILL OWN INTEGRITY AND GOVERNANCE OF A SYSTEM/SOFTWARE SOLUTION, INCLUDING BEST PRACTICES FOR DELIVERING SERVICES. IN ADDITION, THE RESOURCE WILL DEVELOP, DEPLOY AND SUPPORT INFRASTRUCTURES, APPLICATIONS, SOFTWARE SOLUTIONS AND TECHNOLOGY INITIATIVES FROM AN ARCHITECTURAL AND OPERATIONAL PERSPECTIVE IN CONJUNCTION WITH EXISTING STANDARDS AND METHODS OF DELIVERY.
 
 THE RESOURCE WILL BE AN SR. IT SPECIALIST IN SUPPORT OF THE IEP 1.5 PORTALS PROJECT & PRIME TASK 3 PROGRAM.
 
 REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS: 
   PROVIDING HANDS-ON ANALYSIS OF ISSUES, ISSUE REPORTING, AND INCIDENT MANAGEMENT.
   PROVIDING/IMPLEMENTING BEST PRACTICES FOR JBOSS AND APACHE ADMINISTRATION.
   OWN INTEGRITY, GOVERNANCE, ADMINISTRATION AND MAINTENANCE OF THE EXISTING APACHE AND JBOSS WEB APPLICATION PLATFORM.
   PERFORM PERIODIC MAINTENANCE AND UPDATES TO CURRENT SYSTEM OPERATIONS AND MAINTENANCE SCRIPTING/PROGRAMMING, THROUGHOUT THE LIFE OF THE PROJECT.
   DEVELOP, DEPLOY AND SUPPORT INFRASTRUCTURES, APPLICATIONS, SOFTWARE SOLUTIONS AND TECHNOLOGY INITIATIVES FROM AN ARCHITECTURAL AND OPERATIONAL
 PERSPECTIVE IN CONJUNCTION WITH EXISTING STANDARDS AND METHODS OF DELIVERY.
   SUPPORT TECHNICAL ESCALATION OF L3/ADVANCED ISSUES FOR PROBLEM RESOLUTION. APPLY DEEP KNOWLEDGE OF INDUSTRY STANDARDS AND VENDOR CERTIFICATIONS.
 
 
 MICHAEL MUNOSCANO   THE RESOURCE WILL BE PRIMARILY RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DESIGN, CONFIGURATION AND IMPLEMENTATION OF DATA STORAGE ENVIRONMENT WITH PARTICULAR EMPHASIS ON NETWORK ATTACHED STORAGE AND RELATED CONNECTIVITY. THE ROLE WILL PROVIDE BOTH GUIDANCE AND HANDS ON BUILD SUPPORT.
 
 THE RESOURCE WILL BE AN IT SPECIALIST IN SUPPORT OF THE IEP 1.5 PORTALS PROJECT & PRIME TASK 3 PROGRAM. 
 
 REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS:
   SUPPORT RAID DEVELOPMENT
   FORM AGGREGATE FLEXIBLE VOLUMES TO STORE USER ACCESSIBLE DATA
   PROVIDE INPUT ON FILE-BASED PROTOCOLS SUCH AS NFS, CIFS, FTP, TFTP, AND HTTP TO SUPPORT NETWORK STORAGE
   PROVIDE INPUT ON BLOCK-BASED PROTOCOLS SUCH AS FIBRE CHANNEL (FC), FIBRE CHANNEL OVER ETHERNET (FCOE) AND ISCSI
   PROVIDE EXPERT INPUT ON BOOT PROCEDURES TO OPTIMIZE HIGH AND LOW LEVEL STORAGE FUNCTIONS
   DESIGN WAFL, AS A ROBUST VERSIONING FILE SYSTEM, PROVIDING SNAPSHOTS, WHICH ALLOW END-USERS TO SEE EARLIER VERSIONS OF FILES IN THE FILE SYSTEM
   STORAGE TECHNOLOGIES
   NETAPP
   BACKUP STRATEGIES   NETBACKUP
   INFRASTRUCTURE AND DATACENTER TECHNOLOGIES AND OPERATIONS

subaward_description:
3.1  TASK 1 PROGRAM / PROJECT MANAGEMENT SUPPORT SUPPORT IS ANTICIPATED FOR DEVELOPING AND MAINTAINING VARIOUS PROJECT MANAGEMENT DOCUMENTS NEEDED TO EFFECTIVELY MANAGE THIS EFFORT.  SPECIFIC RESPONSIBILITIES ARE EXPECTED TO INCLUDE DEVELOPMENT, REVIEW, COORDINATION, AND UPDATES TO RELATED PROJECT MANAGEMENT DOCUMENTS THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD OF PERFORMANCE. 
 
 3.2  TASK 2 SERVICE MANAGEMENT SUPPORT SUPPORT IS ANTICIPATED FOR PROVIDING APPLICABLE SERVICE MANAGEMENT RELATIVE TO TNET PROGRAM MANAGEMENT OFFICE OPERATIONS.  EXPECTED ACTIVITIES INCLUDE:  
 TNET SERVICES ORDERING FUNCTIONS  ADMINISTRATION AND ENHANCEMENT OF THE SERVICE LEVEL AGREEMENT (SLA) PROCESS AND PERFORMANCE SCORECARD  DEVELOPMENT AND MANAGEMENT OF TNET PMO OPERATIONAL PROCEDURES AND BUSINESS GUIDELINES  SUBMITTING AND MONITORING SERVICE REQUESTS (INTERNALLY FOR NEW OR CHANGES IN SERVICE) AND ENSURING REQUESTS ARE CAREFULLY COORDINATED AND TRACKED BETWEEN BUREAUS AND THE TNET PROGRAM MANAGEMENT OFFICE TO ASSURE IMPLEMENTATION  CHANGE MANAGEMENT FUNCTIONS  SLA VERIFICATION AND VALIDATION FUNCTION  BILLING, INVOICING, AND FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT FUNCTIONS  STATUS REPORTING AND OPERATION PERFORMANCE AND SPECIAL PROJECTS  ASSIST IN MEETING FACILITATION PERTAINING TO SERVICE MANAGEMENT FUNCTION.
 
 3.3  TASK 3 ACQUISITION SUPPORT SUPPORT IS ANTICIPATED FOR PROVIDING PROCUREMENT SUPPORT FOR SERVICES APPLICABLE TO THE TNET PMO S MANAGEMENT OF THE TNET CONTRACT.  EXPECTED ACTIVITIES INCLUDE:  
 ASSIST WITH ACQUISITION STRATEGY SUPPORT  CONDUCT ACQUISITION RISK IDENTIFICATION AND MITIGATION  CONDUCT WORK, PERFORMANCE, AND EVALUATION ANALYSES  FACILITATE WORKING GROUP MEETINGS 
 3.4  TASK 4 COMMUNICATIONS / BUSINESS OPERATIONS SUPPORT SUPPORT IS ANTICIPATED FOR PROVIDING COMMUNICATION AND BUSINESS OPERATIONS SUPPORT.  SPECIFICALLY, COORDINATED COMMUNICATIONS SHALL SUPPORT FLOW OF INFORMATION BOTH WITHIN THE TNET PMO AND TNET STAKEHOLDERS.  ALSO, SUPPORT FOR BUSINESS OPERATIONS SHALL BE INCLUDED AS WELL AS UPDATES TO THE TNET PMO CONCEPT OF OPERATIONS DOCUMENT.  EXPECTED ACTIVITIES INCLUDE:  DEVELOP AND DISTRIBUTE PROGRAM INFORMATION AND PROVIDE EXECUTIVE REPORTING SUPPORT  CREATE MATERIALS AND ORGANIZE SESSIONS TO TRAIN STAKEHOLDERS ON TNET PROCEDURES AND TOOLS  PROVIDE CONTENT FOR WEBBASED COMMUNICATIONS AND ASSIST IN MODIFICATIONS OF WEBPARTS FOR TNET SHAREPOINT SITE  CONDUCT UPDATES TO TNET PMO PROCESS DESCRIPTIONS AND FLOW CHART.

subaward_description: THE IRS HAS ENGAGED ACCENTURE TO ENHANCE THE EXISTING IRS DRUPAL WCMS USING AN ITERATIVE HYBRID AGILE IMPLEMENTATION APPROACH IN SUPPORT OF IRS.GOV FUTURE STATE. THE IRS INTENDS TO LEVERAGE INDUSTRY LEADING PRACTICES AND INNOVATIONS TO IMPROVE ALL FOUR WEBSITES  EFFICIENCY, EFFECTIVENESS, QUALITY, AND PROCESS MATURITY WHILE SATISFYING GROWING DEMANDS FOR SECURE, RELIABLE, TIMELY, AND CUSTOMERCENTRIC WEB SOLUTIONS. IN THIS PROJECT, THE IRS EXPECTS TO FURTHER ENHANCE THE EXISTING SYSTEM TO ACHIEVE MORE FLEXIBILITY IN MANAGING AND PRESENTING WEB CONTENT TO OPTIMIZE WEBSITE CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE ACROSS A VARIETY OF MODERN DIGITAL DEVICES, INCLUDING MOBILE.  THE CONTRACTOR SHALL SUPPORT THE FRONTEND DEVELOPMENT AND TEST MANAGEMENT ENHANCEMENTS EFFORTS IN SUPPORT OF IRS.GOV FUTURE STATE VISION IN A HYBRIDAGILE IMPLEMENTATION.    AS PART OF THE APPLICATION DEVELOPMENT TEAM, WILL BUILD THE WCMS AND SUPPORTING SYSTEMS PER THE REQUIREMENTS AND DESIGN DOCUMENTATION APPROVED IN THE BUSINESS CAPABILITIES FOCUSING ON THE FOLLOWING MAIN FUNCTIONAL CATEGORIES: O PUBLIC USER INTERFACE  O ADMINISTRATIVE USER INTERFACE  O SEARCH O ANALYTICS   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE AND IRS TO SCOPE, ANALYZE, DESIGN AND IMPLEMENT DESIGN ENHANCEMENTS FOR IRS.GOV   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE AND IRS TO UPDATE DELIVERABLES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO DESIGN DOCUMENTATION, TEST PLANS, TEST RESULTS, RELEASE PLANS/RESULTS   ADHERING TO DRUPAL BEST PRACTICES FOR DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE TO SUPPORT IRS WITH THEIR USER ACCEPTANCE TESTING, REPORTING ON DEFECTS AND MANAGING THE TEST TEAM   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE AND IRS TO MEET 508 COMPLIANCE REQUIREMENTS DURING DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING   WORKING WITH RESPONSIVE DESIGN AND CONSEQUENTLY SUPPORTING RESPONSIVE DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING EFFORTS

subaward_description:
PORTAL SERVICE AND PROGRAM INTEGRATION SERVICES TO OPERATE THE IRS ENVIRONMENT WITHIN SPECIFIED SCOPE, QUALITY,  TIME, AND COST OBJECTIVES.
 
 THIS POSITION REQUIRES A HIGHLY MOTIVATED INDIVIDUAL WHO WILL PROVIDE TECHNOLOGY EXPERT IN THE NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE. THE INDIVIDUAL IN THIS ROLE WILL PROVIDE TECHNICAL DIRECTION, RESOLVE INFRASTRUCTURE TECHNOLOGY ISSUES, PROVIDE NETWORK AND FIREWALL ARCHITECTURE GUIDANCE AND POSSESS THE KNOWLEDGE FOR TECHNICAL INTEGRATION.  DEFINE TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS & DESIGN TO SUPPORT DEFINED BUSINESS REQUIREMENTS, DEVELOP TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE COMPONENTS, PARTICIPATE IN DETAILED DESIGN AND CODE REVIEWS, CONFIGURE AND BUILD INFRASTRUCTURE NETWORK COMPONENTS (SWITCH, ROUTERS, FIREWALL), PARTICIPATE IN REVIEWS AND RESOLVES SYSTEM PERFORMANCE AND CONSUMPTION ISSUES, REVIEW INFRASTRUCTURE TEST PLANS, AND PROVIDE TECHNICAL GUIDANCE.  DEFINE AND ENSURE ADHERENCE TO ARCHITECTURE STANDARDS AND ENSURES THE PROPER TECHNICAL DESIGN DECISIONS ARE BEING MADE.
 
 RESPONSIBILITIES:
   DESIGN AND IMPLEMENT THE NETWORK AND SECURITY INFRASTRUCTURE FOR THE IRS INFRASTRUCTURE
   BUILD THE LAN AND WAN (MPLS) INFRASTRUCTURE TO RESPOND TO BUSINESS AND TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS; WORKING WITH OTHER TEAMS (E.G.,
 SERVER, SECURITY) ON THE DESIGN AND INSTALLATION OF NEW IT INFRASTRUCTURE SERVICES
   RECOMMENDS NETWORK DESIGNS AND CONFIGURATION IMPROVEMENTS TO CONFORM TO NEW INDUSTRY TRENDS AS IT APPLIES TO NETWORK AND
 SECURITY AREAS.
   RESPONSIBLE FOR ENSURING THAT THE NETWORK AND SECURITY DEVICES ARE CONFIGURED IN COMPLIANCE TO THE CLIENT S SECURITY POLICIES AND
 REQUIREMENTS
   CONTRIBUTE TO KNOWLEDGE TRANSFER TO NETWORK OPERATIONS RESOURCES AROUND NEW NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE.

subaward_description:
THE CONTRACTOR SHALL:
   PERFORM SYSTEM SECURITY PLAN (SSP) COMPLIANCE REVIEW TO SUPPORT THE SSP COMPLIANCE STATUS REPORT AND SECURITY ASSESSMENT PLAN (SAP).
   PERFORM SECURITY CONTROL ASSESSMENT TO SUPPORT THE SECURITY ASSESSMENT REPORT.
   VALIDATE SSP AND CORRESPONDING SECURITY CONTROL IMPLEMENTATION STATEMENTS.
   PROVIDE SUPPORT SERVICES THROUGHOUT THE FEDRAMP PMO COMPLETENESS CHECK.
   PROVIDE ASSESSMENT SUPPORT SERVICES TO ADDRESS PLAN OF ACTION AND MILESTONES (POA&M) FINDINGS, AND OPEN TESTING ACTIVITIES.
   PERFORM ANY NECESSARY INTERVIEWS REQUIRED FOR INFORMATION GATHERING DURING THE ASSESSMENTS, SCANS, DOCUMENTATION AND POLICY REVIEWS.
   PROVIDE SUPPORT SERVICES TO ADDRESS JOINT AUTHORITY BOARD (JAB) REVIEW QUESTIONS, BRIEFINGS, AND ANY REQUIRED MEETINGS WITH THE CLOUD SERVICES PROVIDER (CSP), JAB, AND FEDRAMP PMO
   PERFORM ADDITIONAL TESTING, REMEDIATION, AND VALIDATION OF WEAKNESSES IDENTIFIED FOLLOWING JAB REVIEW.
   TRACK ALL ASSOCIATED POST-REMEDIATION ACTIVITIES AND REPORT PROGRESS WEEKLY TO THE SECURITY LEAD.
   WORK TO FINALIZE ANY NECESSARY SECURITY DOCUMENTATION, ARTIFACTS, AND CONTROL COMPLIANCE.
   ENSURE ALL JAB REVIEW COMMENTS AND FEEDBACK ARE ADDRESSED.
   PROVIDE SUPPORT TO REMEDIATE PO&AM FINDINGS POST-ASSESSMENT AND PRIOR TO THE ATO TO AN ACCEPTABLE LEVEL, AS DEFINED BY THE AUTHORIZING OFFICIAL (AO), FOR AO ACCEPTANCE.
   PREPARE FINAL SECURITY AUTHORIZATION PACKAGE FOR FINAL SUBMISSION.
 
 DELIVERABLES:
 3PAO PROJECT SCHEDULE
 SECURITY ASSESSMENT PLAN
 SECURITY ASSESSMENT REPORT

subaward_description: THE IRS HAS ENGAGED ACCENTURE TO ENHANCE THE EXISTING IRS DRUPAL WCMS USING AN ITERATIVE HYBRID AGILE IMPLEMENTATION APPROACH IN SUPPORT OF IRS.GOV FUTURE STATE. THE IRS INTENDS TO LEVERAGE INDUSTRY LEADING PRACTICES AND INNOVATIONS TO IMPROVE ALL FOUR WEBSITES  EFFICIENCY, EFFECTIVENESS, QUALITY, AND PROCESS MATURITY WHILE SATISFYING GROWING DEMANDS FOR SECURE, RELIABLE, TIMELY, AND CUSTOMER-CENTRIC WEB SOLUTIONS. IN THIS PROJECT, THE IRS EXPECTS TO FURTHER ENHANCE THE EXISTING SYSTEM TO ACHIEVE MORE FLEXIBILITY IN MANAGING AND PRESENTING WEB CONTENT TO OPTIMIZE WEBSITE CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE ACROSS A VARIETY OF MODERN DIGITAL DEVICES, INCLUDING MOBILE.  THE CONTRACTOR SHALL SUPPORT THE FRONT-END DEVELOPMENT AND TEST MANAGEMENT ENHANCEMENTS EFFORTS IN SUPPORT OF IRS.GOV FUTURE STATE VISION IN A HYBRID-AGILE IMPLEMENTATION.    AS PART OF THE APPLICATION DEVELOPMENT TEAM, WILL BUILD THE WCMS AND SUPPORTING SYSTEMS PER THE REQUIREMENTS AND DESIGN DOCUMENTATION APPROVED IN THE BUSINESS CAPABILITIES FOCUSING ON THE FOLLOWING MAIN FUNCTIONAL CATEGORIES: O PUBLIC USER INTERFACE  O ADMINISTRATIVE USER INTERFACE  O SEARCH O ANALYTICS   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE AND IRS TO SCOPE, ANALYZE, DESIGN AND IMPLEMENT DESIGN ENHANCEMENTS FOR IRS.GOV   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE AND IRS TO UPDATE DELIVERABLES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO DESIGN DOCUMENTATION, TEST PLANS, TEST RESULTS, RELEASE PLANS/RESULTS   ADHERING TO DRUPAL BEST PRACTICES FOR DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE TO SUPPORT IRS WITH THEIR USER ACCEPTANCE TESTING, REPORTING ON DEFECTS AND MANAGING THE TEST TEAM   WORKING WITH ACCENTURE AND IRS TO MEET 508 COMPLIANCE REQUIREMENTS DURING DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING   WORKING WITH RESPONSIVE DESIGN AND CONSEQUENTLY SUPPORTING RESPONSIVE DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING EFFORTS

subaward_description:
THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS), ENTERPRISE TECHNOLOGY IMPLEMENTATION DIVISION (ETI), HAS EMBARKED ON A TRANSFORMATION PROGRAM FOR ITS WEB PORTALS REFERRED TO AS THE INTEGRATED ENTERPRISE PORTALS (IEP). THE IRS SEEKS A COMPREHENSIVE CONTRACT VEHICLE DESIGNED TO ENABLE FLEXIBILITY TO MANAGE THE EXISTING SERVICES AND ACCOMMODATE THE CHANGING DYNAMICS OF THE REQUIREMENTS DUE TO CONGRESSIONAL MANDATES PLACED ON THE IRS.
 
 THE IEP IS A FULLY SCALABLE, MANAGED PRIVATE, VIRTUALIZED INFRASTRUCTURE CAPABILITY DEDICATED TO THE IRS THAT PROVIDES TECHNOLOGY SERVICES TO INTERNAL AND EXTERNAL USERS. FOR PURPOSES OF THIS AGREEMENT,  PRIVATE  MEANS ACQUIA S ACE PRODUCT WHICH USES A SHARED CONTROL PLANE (INSIGHT, HOSTING MASTER, ETC.), I.E. ACQUIA SHIELD/DEDICATED VPC. THE IEP PLAYS A MISSION CRITICAL ROLE IN SERVING TAX PAYERS, TAX PREPARERS AND EMPLOYEES. THE IEP PROVIDES FULLY INTEGRATED CORE SERVICES, INCLUDING IT INFRASTRUCTURE, OPERATIONS, SECURITY, APPLICATION, INTEGRATION AND SUPPORT, AND PROGRAM MANAGEMENT SERVICES, TO ESTABLISH A FULLY INTEGRATED ROBUST PLATFORM THAT SUPPORTS MULTIPLE WORKLOADS, ALSO REFERRED TO AS PORTALS AND MAJOR APPLICATIONS, AND APPLICATION STYLES. (REFER TO THE SOLICITATION SECTION J, ATTACHMENT C.1, CURRENT STATE OF THE PORTALS AND HELP DESK ENVIRONMENTS, FOR DETAILS OF THE EXISTING LANDSCAPE).
 
 FOUR DISTINCT IRS PORTALS UNDER THE INTEGRATED ENTERPRISE PORTAL (IEP) UMBRELLA CURRENTLY SUPPORT THE IRS USER COMMUNITIES: THE PUBLIC USER PORTAL (PUP) (ALSO KNOWN AS IRS.GOV), THE REGISTERED USER PORTAL (RUP), THE EMPLOYEE USER PORTAL (EUP), AND THE TRANSACTION PORTAL ENVIRONMENT (TPE), EACH WITH ITS OWN INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (IT) INFRASTRUCTURE AND GOVERNANCE. THESE PORTALS ARE DESCRIBED BELOW:
 
   THE PUP IS THE IRS EXTERNAL OR INTERNET PORTAL--IRS.GOV, WHICH ALLOWS UNRESTRICTED PUBLIC ACCESS TO NON-SENSITIVE MATERIALS AND APPLICATIONS FORMS, INSTRUCTIONS, NEWS, AND TAX CALCULATORS. NO AUTHENTICATION IS REQUIRED FOR ACCESS TO ANY MATERIALS ON THE IEP PUP. FOR CLARITY, ACQUIA SCOPE UNDER THIS AGREEMENT IS LIMITED TO THIS PUBLIC USER PORTAL (PUP) (ALSO KNOWN AS IRS.GOV).
 
   THE RUP IS THE IRS EXTERNAL PORTAL THAT ALLOWS REGISTERED INDIVIDUALS AND THIRD PARTY USERS (COLLECTIVELY,  PARTNERS    REGISTRATION AND LOGIN AUTHENTICATION REQUIRED) AND OTHER INDIVIDUAL TAXPAYERS OR THEIR REPRESENTATIVES ACCESS FOR INTERACTION WITH SELECTED TAX PROCESSING AND OTHER SENSITIVE SYSTEMS, APPLICATIONS, AND DATA.
 
   THE EUP IS THE INTERNAL IRS PORTAL THAT ALLOWS IRS EMPLOYEE USERS TO ACCESS IRS DATA AND SYSTEMS, SUCH AS TAX ADMINISTRATION PROCESSING SYSTEMS, FINANCIAL INFORMATION SYSTEMS, AND OTHER DATA AND APPLICATIONS, INCLUDING MISSION CRITICAL APPLICATIONS. REGISTRATION AND AUTHENTICATION ARE REQUIRED FOR ACCESS TO SENSITIVE AND MISSION CRITICAL APPLICATIONS.
 
   THE TPE HOSTS INFORMATION ON THE AFFORDABLE CARE ACT (ACA) LEGISLATION WHICH ENABLES THE IRS TO SUPPORT INITIAL ENROLLMENT VIA THE ACA HEALTH INSURANCE MARKETPLACE. IEP TPE HAS PROCESSED MORE THAN 45 MILLION TRANSACTIONS BETWEEN THE US DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES (HHS) CENTER FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES AND THE IRS, WHICH HAS ALLOWED MORE THAN 7 MILLION AMERICANS TO ENROLL SUCCESSFULLY VIA THE ACA HEALTH INSURANCE MARKETPLACES.
  
 
 
 THE GOVERNMENT IS SEEKING CONTRACTOR SUPPORT TO PROVIDE FULLY MANAGED, SCALABLE WEB HOSTING SERVICES FOR THE IRS  EXTERNAL STAKEHOLDERS AND ITS INTERNAL CUSTOMERS. THE SELECTED CONTRACTOR WILL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR PROVIDING ALL LABOR, HARDWARE, SOFTWARE, EQUIPMENT, MATERIALS, COMMUNICATIONS, FACILITIES, AND OTHER NECESSARY IT INFRASTRUCTURE TO IMPLEMENT, DEPLOY, OPERATE, MANAGE, AND SUPPORT THE EXISTING WEBSITES IN A FEDERAL INFORMATION SECURITY MANAGEMENT ACT (FISMA) MODERATE SECURE ENVIRONMENT, AS WELL AS ITS UNDERLYING TECHNOLOGY INFRASTRUCTURE.
